docs.abstract: While NATO celebrates turning 70, a squabble between Washington and Ankara over fighter jets and missile systems threatens to spoil the party.
docs.snippet: While NATO celebrates turning 70, a squabble between Washington and Ankara over fighter jets and missile systems threatens to spoil the party.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The NATO secretary general gave a strong defense of the 70-year-old military alliance between Europe and the United States, using a high-profile appearance before a joint session of Congress on Wednesday to urge allies to stand up to a more assertive Russia.

headline.main: In Rare Speech to Congress, NATO Leader Says Allies Must Deter Moscow
headline.print_headline: NATO Chief Says Allies Must Deter Russian Acts

docs.abstract: In a political career that stretches 50 years, Joseph R. Biden Jr. has been a master of an in-your-space intimacy that is proving to be a liability.
docs.snippet: In a political career that stretches 50 years, Joseph R. Biden Jr. has been a master of an in-your-space intimacy that is proving to be a liability.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Joseph R. Biden Jr. came up in politics as an old-school backslapper whose greatest strength was his ability to connect. He doled out handshakes and hugs to friends and strangers alike, and his tendency to lavish his affections on women and girls was so central to his persona that it became fodder for late-night television jokes.

headline.main: Biden’s Tactile Politics Threaten His Return in the #MeToo Era
headline.print_headline: A Master of Tactile Politics Finds Cold Shoulders

byline.original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Sydney Ember

docs.abstract: The president’s former fixer has millions of documents and recordings that he thinks would interest Congress. But he is due to report to prison on May 6.
docs.snippet: The president’s former fixer has millions of documents and recordings that he thinks would interest Congress. But he is due to report to prison on May 6.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Lawyers for Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s former personal lawyer and fixer, told congressional lawmakers in a letter on Thursday that Mr. Cohen can best help their oversight inquiries if he remains out of prison to sift through millions of his documents — and they asked the help of Democrats in persuading prosecutors to help him do so.

headline.main: Michael Cohen’s Lawyers Say He Could Aid Trump Inquiries, if Only He Had More Time Out of Prison
headline.print_headline: Offer to Aid Trump Inquiries, If Only Prison Can Be Put Off

docs.abstract: The potential nomination signals the second time in weeks that the president has considered someone with partisan views for the Fed.
docs.snippet: The potential nomination signals the second time in weeks that the president has considered someone with partisan views for the Fed.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump said on Thursday that he planned to nominate Herman Cain, who abandoned his 2012 presidential bid in the face of escalating accusations of sexual misconduct, for a seat on the Federal Reserve Board.

headline.main: Trump Says He Wants Herman Cain, Former Pizza Executive, for Fed Board
headline.print_headline: Trump Favors Pizza Magnate For Fed Board

docs.abstract: The lawyer’s argument foreshadows a likely and far-reaching legal fight over President Trump’s tax returns that could wind up in the Supreme Court.
docs.snippet: The lawyer’s argument foreshadows a likely and far-reaching legal fight over President Trump’s tax returns that could wind up in the Supreme Court.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s personal lawyer on Friday asserted Mr. Trump’s right as a citizen to keep his tax returns private and told the Treasury Department not to hand the returns over to House Democrats, foreshadowing what has the potential to be a far-reaching legal fight that could reach the Supreme Court.

headline.main: Trump Lawyer Asserts President’s Right to Keep Tax Returns Private
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Lawyer Signals a Battle On Tax Returns

docs.abstract: Her departure was abrupt but hardly unforeseen as the latest senior official to leave the administration because of frustrations with the president, or his obvious disappointment.
docs.snippet: Her departure was abrupt but hardly unforeseen as the latest senior official to leave the administration because of frustrations with the president, or his obvious disappointment.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In recent months, Kirstjen Nielsen, the secretary of homeland security, had become a regular presence eating dinner at the Trump International Hotel. She had been heckled and booed when dining out after becoming the face of some of President Trump’s most hard-line immigration policies, like family separations, and her affinity for the hotel, a gathering place for the president’s supporters, seemed like a sign that she felt safer on the inside.

headline.main: Kirstjen Nielsen Is the Latest Trump Official to Meet an Unceremonious End
headline.print_headline: Common Fate for Trump Officials: Abrupt, Unceremonious Departure

byline.original: By Annie Karni and Maggie Haberman

docs.abstract: The Treasury secretary has agreed to recuse himself from matters that could benefit his wife’s film business.
docs.snippet: The Treasury secretary has agreed to recuse himself from matters that could benefit his wife’s film business.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The top federal ethics watchdog said on Thursday that Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin’s sale of his stake in a film production business to his wife did not comply with federal ethics rules, and it would not certify his 2018 financial disclosure report as a result.

headline.main: U.S. Ethics Office Declines to Certify Mnuchin’s Financial Disclosure
headline.print_headline: Film Deal By Mnuchin Broke Rules At Treasury

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Investigators for the special counsel spent months trying to get answers from President Trump: what he knew about a meeting between senior campaign aides and Russians; about changes to the Republican Party platform making it more Russia-friendly; about his associates’ outreach to WikiLeaks as it prepared to publish Democratic emails stolen by Russian hackers.

headline.main: Congress Waits as Barr Blacks Out Parts of Mueller Report
